article.headline: Fairfield 65, Canisius 51
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Yorel Hawkins had a career-high 18 points, and Lyndon Jordan added 12 to lead Fairfield to a 65-51 win over Canisius on Friday. Hawkins also added 10 rebounds, and Ryan Olander contributed 11 points for the Stags (15-9, 8-5 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Fairfield was up 32-30 three minutes into the second half. Then the Stags began pulling away with a 13-5 run, capped by a 10-foot jumper from Hawkins that made it 45-35 with 13:27 left. Hawkins' two free throws stretched Fairfield's lead to 55-42 with 5:08 to go. Frank Turner had 20 points, and Greg Logins added 10 for Canisius (7-16, 2-11). The Golden Griffins struggled offensively, shooting only 30 percent from the floor and 56 percent from the free throw line.
